        {
          "class": "DepictionMarkdownView",
          "markdown": "**AntiDarkSword** protects your device from hidden web browser exploits and silent iMessage attacks (like Coruna, DarkSword, and BLASTPASS).",
          "useRawFormat": false
        },
        {
          "class": "DepictionSpacerView",
          "spacing": 8
        },
        {
          "class": "DepictionSeparatorView"
        },
        {
          "class": "DepictionSubheaderView",
          "title": "Protection Layers",
          "useBoldText": true
        },
        {
          "class": "DepictionMarkdownView",
          "markdown": "• **Browser Protection** — Makes web browsing safer by reducing areas attackers can target.\n\n• **iMessage Security** — Blocks silent attacks by stopping dangerous file downloads and risky attachment previews (like PDFs and images).\n\n• **Content Blocking** — Automatically blocks unsafe content in messaging and mail apps.\n\n• **Device Cloaking** — Spoofs environments that are not vulnerable causing most payloads to abort.\n\n• **Decoy System** — Tricks attackers into thinking your device is a test virtual machine, stopping many advanced attacks in their tracks.\n\n• **Background Service Protection** — Secures core system services (like message syncing) when using higher security levels.",
          "useRawFormat": false
        },
        {
          "class": "DepictionSeparatorView"
        },
        {
          "class": "DepictionSubheaderView",
          "title": "Auto-Protect Levels",
          "useBoldText": true
        },
        {
          "class": "DepictionMarkdownView",
          "markdown": "• **Level 1** — Web browsers, mail, messaging, and web-heavy apps.\n\n• **Level 2** — Everything in Level 1, plus social media and entertainment apps.\n\n• **Level 3** — Everything in Level 2, plus background system services.\n\n*Note: You can easily set custom rules to override these levels for specific apps if you need to.*",
          "useRawFormat": false
        },
